Explanation:

We use a simple formula to calculate the total number of ways. We iterate from 1 to x (the number of stages) and multiply the result by (n/i), where n is the number of performers and i is the current iteration value. Finally, multiply the result by y (the maximum score) and take the modulo with 1000000007 (a prime number chosen for its efficiency in modular arithmetic operations). The time complexity is O(x) because we iterate x times. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the result variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm performs only simple arithmetic operations.

